column42: The animals near our testing area were pretty much only seagulls. The seagulls would flow on the river near the ocean, and  then fly back to the top.  It was very funny. However,  they flew away when we went too close. The main plant near our area was ice plant. We tried to kill some of the ice plant because ice plant is an invasive species and it is bad for our environment.
